Varying was removed when other shader types such as geometry shaders were introduced. HyperBeetle only supports vertex and fragment shaders. in and out type qualifiers are conditionally removed based on shader stages. This changes their semantic meaning. in now ALWAYS refers to a vertex shader input. out now ALWAYS refers to a fragment shader output. Varying is used to transfer values between the two shaders. These will be changed to the correct type qualifier at runtime. in vec3 inPosition = 0; // inout assignment
in vec2 inTexCoord = 1; // inout assignment varying vec2 vTexCoord; out vec4 outColor = 0; // inout assignment uniform sampler2D uAlbedo; [[vert]] void main(void) { gl_Position = vec4(inPosition, 1.0); vTexCoord = inTexCoord;
}
[[frag]] void main(void) { outColor = texture(uAlbedo, vTexCoord);
}
